{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb88666f5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1383e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1383e"},"text":"§ 1383e.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Treatment referrals for individuals with alcoholism or drug addiction condition","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of any individual whose benefits under this subchapter are paid to a repre­sentative payee pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1383/a/2/A/ii/II"},"text":"section 1383(a)(2)(A)(ii)(II) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Commissioner of Social Security shall refer such individual to the appropriate State agency administering the State plan for substance abuse treatment services approved under subpart II of part B of title XIX of the Public Health Service Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300x–21"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 300x–21","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb88666f6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title XVI, § 1636, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/121/tI/s105/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–121, title I, § 105(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-03-29"},"text":"Mar. 29, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/854"},"text":"110 Stat. 854","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb88666f7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb88666f8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"chi